data.text:
UTAH: Walk-on joined the team in fall of 2015 … cornerback has two years remaining on his NCAA clock.

2015–Redshirt.

PRIOR TO UTAH: Played at Santa Monica College from 2013-14 … helped SMC win two American Pacific Conference titles with undefeated records in league play … played defensive back in 2013 (four games) and running back in 2014 (10 games) … 25 carries for 115 yards in 2014 and also had 16 receptions for 229 yards (14.3 ypc) and five touchdowns … in 2013, he totaled four tackles … 29-yard kickoff return against Glendale … led Skyline HS (Wash.) to 4A state titles in 2009 and 2011 … King County 4A Crest Division first team cornerback and second team running back in 2011 … second-team all-league cornerback in 2010 … rushed for 751 yards and eight touchdowns on 133 carries in 2011 … also caught 25 receptions for 531 yards and seven TDs his senior season … scored three touchdowns (two receiving and one rushing) with 247 all-purpose yards against Central Valley in the state quarterfinals … intercepted a two-point conversion attempt by Curtis HS in the state title game … competed in track & field.

PERSONAL: Son of Danny and Ida Greene … father played wide receiver at Washington from 1981-84 and was a team captain of 11-1 squad that beat Oklahoma in the Orange Bowl … father also played in the NFL for the Seattle Seahawks in 1985 … uncle, Scott Garnett, played at Washington Huskies prior to an NFL career with the Buffalo Bills, San Diego Chargers, San Francisco 49ers and Denver Broncos … double major in international studies and Japanese.
